This paper deals with performance measures of networked message processing systems, which are typically studied in the field of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves stochastic processes and Laplace transforms, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions admission controls in bufferless systems, which could be related to queueing theory (cs.PF). Finally, the paper discusses future work on assessing enqueueing policies, which could involve optimization and decision-making techniques (cs.MA).
